{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775892014786,"sessionID":"ses_2849df3aeffec83aH4jGcJVeZm","part":{"id":"prt_d7b68e9bf001F6CW1Xp5OWcTIU","messageID":"msg_d7b68dc5a0019WzfV3S3sPXVPI","sessionID":"ses_2849df3aeffec83aH4jGcJVeZm","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_70f8e1b3cab44f84ad595a75","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# AgentCube E2E Tests\n\nThis directory contains comprehensive end-to-end tests for the AgentCube platform.\n\n## Table of Contents\n\n- [Overview](#overview)\n- [Requirements](#requirements)\n- [Quick Start](#quick-start)\n- [Test Structure](#test-structure)\n- [Configuration](#configuration)\n- [Running Tests](#running-tests)\n- [Test Fixtures](#test-fixtures)\n- [Troubleshooting](#troubleshooting)\n- [Writing New Tests](#writing-new-tests)\n\n## Overview\n\nThe E2E test suite validates the complete AgentCube platform including:\n\n- **Workload Manager**: Health checks, session management, metrics\n- **Router**: Health checks, agent invocation, load balancing\n- **Code Interpreter**: Code execution, session lifecycle, warm pool\n- **Kubernetes Integration**: Namespace isolation, resource quotas, RBAC\n- **Agent Runtimes**: Echo agent, stress test agent, multi-session agent\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Software Requirements\n\n- **Go** 1.23+\n- **Python** 3.10+\n- **Kind** v0.30.0+\n- **Helm** 3.x\n- **Docker** 20.10+\n- **kubectl** 1.28+\n\n### System Requirements\n\n- 4+ CPU cores recommended\n- 8GB+ RAM recommended\n- Docker daemon running\n\n## Quick Start\n\nRun the complete E2E test suite:\n\n```bash\n# Full test suite (creates Kind cluster, runs tests, cleans up)\nmake e2e\n\n# Or run the script directly\n./test/e2e/run_e2e.sh\n```\n\n## Test Structure\n\n```\ntest/e2e/\n├── config.env                    # Environment configuration\n├── helpers.go                    # Go test helpers\n├── e2e_test.go                   # Go E2E tests\n├── __init__.py                   # Python package init\n├── test_codeinterpreter.py       # Python E2E tests\n├── run_e2e.sh                    # Test runner script\n├── README.md                     # This file\n└── fixtures/\n    ├── echo_agent.yaml           # Echo agent fixture\n    ├── e2e_code_interpreter.yaml # Basic code interpreter\n    ├── e2e_code_interpreter_warmpool.yaml  # Warm pool interpreter\n    ├── stress_test_agent.yaml    # Stress test agent\n    ├── multi_session_agent.yaml  # Multi-session agent\n    └── e2e_advanced_interpreter.yaml # Advanced interpreter\n```\n\n## Configuration\n\n### Environment Variables\n\n| Variable | Default | Description |\n|----------|---------|-------------|\n| `E2E_CLUSTER_NAME` | `agentcube-e2e` | Kind cluster name |\n| `E2E_CLEAN_CLUSTER` | `true` | Delete cluster before tests |\n| `E2E_SKIP_SETUP` | `false` | Skip cluster setup |\n| `E2E_PRESERVE_CLUSTER` | `false` | Keep cluster after tests |\n| `E2E_DEBUG` | `false` | Enable debug logging |\n| `AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE` | `agentcube` | Kubernetes namespace |\n| `AGENT_SANDBOX_VERSION` | `v0.1.1` | Agent sandbox version |\n| `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_LOCAL_PORT` | `8080` | Workload manager port |\n| `ROUTER_LOCAL_PORT` | `8081` | Router port |\n| `REDIS_IMAGE` | `redis:7-alpine` | Redis image |\n| `E2E_VENV_DIR` | `/tmp/agentcube-e2e-venv` | Python venv path |\n| `ARTIFACTS_PATH` | `${PWD}/e2e-logs` | Test artifacts path |\n| `E2E_TIMEOUT` | `30s` | HTTP request timeout |\n| `E2E_CONCURRENCY` | `5` | Concurrent test workers |\n\n### Using Configuration File\n\nSource the configuration file:\n\n```bash\nsource test/e2e/config.env\nexport E2E_CLUSTER_NAME=my-e2e-cluster\n./test/e2e/run_e2e.sh\n```\n\n## Running Tests\n\n### Full Test Suite\n\n```bash\n# Run everything\nmake e2e\n\n# With options\n./test/e2e/run_e2e.sh --skip-setup --preserve-cluster --debug\n```\n\n### Individual Test Suites\n\n```bash\n# Go tests only\nexport WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL=http://localhost:8080\nexport ROUTER_URL=http://localhost:8081\nexport API_TOKEN=$(kubectl -n agentcube create token e2e-test --duration=24h)\ngo test -v ./test/e2e/...\n\n# Python tests only\ncd test/e2e\npython test_codeinterpreter.py --verbose\n```\n\n### Manual Testing\n\n```bash\n# Set up port forwarding\nkubectl -n agentcube port-forward svc/workloadmanager 8080:8080 &\nkubectl -n agentcube port-forward svc/agentcube-router 8081:8080 &\n\n# Test health endpoints\ncurl http://localhost:8080/health\ncurl http://localhost:8081/health/live\n\n# Test agent invocation\ncurl -X POST http://localhost:8081/invoke/echo-agent \\\n  -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" \\\n  -d '{\"message\": \"Hello!\"}'\n```\n\n## Test Fixtures\n\n### Echo Agent\n\nSimple agent that echoes back received messages.\n\n```yaml\nkubectl apply -f test/e2e/echo_agent.yaml\n```\n\n### Code Interpreter\n\nPython code execution environment.\n\n```yaml\nkubectl apply -f test/e2e/e2e_code_interpreter.yaml\n```\n\n### Warm Pool Interpreter\n\nCode interpreter with pre-warmed sessions for low latency.\n\n```yaml\nkubectl apply -f test/e2e/e2e_code_interpreter_warmpool.yaml\n```\n\n### Stress Test Agent\n\nAgent designed for load testing with multiple replicas.\n\n```yaml\nkubectl apply -f test/e2e/stress_test_agent.yaml\n```\n\n### Multi-Session Agent\n\nAgent that maintains state across multiple sessions.\n\n```yaml\nkubectl apply -f test/e2e/multi_session_agent.yaml\n```\n\n## Troubleshooting\n\n### Test Failures\n\n1. **Check logs**:\n   ```bash\n   ./test/e2e/run_e2e.sh 2>&1 | tee e2e.log\n   ```\n\n2. **View component logs**:\n   ```bash\n   kubectl -n agentcube logs -l app=workloadmanager\n   kubectl -n agentcube logs -l app=agentcube-router\n   ```\n\n3. **Check pod status**:\n   ```bash\n   kubectl -n agentcube get pods -o wide\n   kubectl -n agentcube describe pod -l app=workloadmanager\n   ```\n\n4. **View events**:\n   ```bash\n   kubectl -n agentcube get events --sort-by='.lastTimestamp'\n   ```\n\n### Common Issues\n\n#### Port Already in Use\n\n```bash\n# Kill existing port-forward processes\npkill -f \"kubectl.*port-forward\"\n\n# Or use different ports\nexport WORKLOAD_MANAGER_LOCAL_PORT=9080\nexport ROUTER_LOCAL_PORT=9081\n```\n\n#### Cluster Creation Fails\n\n```bash\n# Delete existing cluster\nkind delete cluster --name agentcube-e2e\n\n# Recreate\nkind create cluster --name agentcube-e2e\n```\n\n#### Image Pull Errors\n\n```bash\n# Build images\nmake docker-build\nmake docker-build-router\n\n# Load to Kind\nkind load docker-image workloadmanager:latest --name agentcube-e2e\nkind load docker-image agentcube-router:latest --name agentcube-e2e\n```\n\n### Collecting Artifacts\n\nOn failure, artifacts are automatically collected to `$ARTIFACTS_PATH`:\n\n- Component logs\n- Pod descriptions\n- Kubernetes events\n- Test reports\n- Metrics snapshots\n\n```bash\n# View artifacts\nls -la $ARTIFACTS_PATH\ncat $ARTIFACTS_PATH/test_report_*.md\n```\n\n## Writing New Tests\n\n### Go Tests\n\n```go\nfunc TestMyFeature(t *testing.T) {\n    // Setup\n    payload := map[string]string{\n        \"message\": \"Test message\",\n    }\n    body, _ := json.Marshal(payload)\n    \n    // Execute\n    req, _ := http.NewRequest(\"POST\", routerURL+\"/invoke/my-agent\", bytes.NewReader(body))\n    req.Header.Set(\"Content-Type\", \"application/json\")\n    resp, err := client.Do(req)\n    \n    // Assert\n    if err != nil {\n        t.Fatalf(\"Request failed: %v\", err)\n    }\n    defer resp.Body.Close()\n    \n    if resp.StatusCode != http.StatusOK {\n        t.Fatalf(\"Expected 200, got %d\", resp.StatusCode)\n    }\n    \n    var result map[string]interface{}\n    json.NewDecoder(resp.Body).Decode(&result)\n    \n    if result[\"status\"] != \"success\" {\n        t.Errorf(\"Expected success status\")\n    }\n}\n```\n\n### Python Tests\n\n```python\ndef test_my_feature(self):\n    \"\"\"Test my feature.\"\"\"\n    payload = {\n        'message': 'Test message'\n    }\n    \n    try:\n        result = self.router_client.request(\n            'POST',\n            '/invoke/my-agent',\n            data=payload\n        )\n        self.assertEqual(result.get('status'), 'success')\n        print(f\"✓ My feature test passed\")\n    except Exception as e:\n        self.fail(f\"My feature test failed: {e}\")\n```\n\n### Test Best Practices\n\n1. **Use descriptive names**: `TestSessionCreationAndDeletion`\n2. **Clean up resources**: Delete sessions, pods, etc.\n3. **Handle errors gracefully**: Use `t.Skip()` for optional features\n4. **Add logging**: Use `t.Logf()` or `print()` for visibility\n5. **Set timeouts**: Prevent hanging tests\n6. **Test edge cases**: Invalid inputs, timeouts, errors\n7. **Use fixtures**: Reusable test data and configurations\n\n## CI/CD Integration\n\n### GitHub Actions\n\n```yaml\n- name: Run E2E Tests\n  run: |\n    make e2e\n  env:\n    E2E_CLEAN_CLUSTER: true\n    ARTIFACTS_PATH: ${{ github.workspace }}/e2e-logs\n\n- name: Upload Artifacts\n  if: always()\n  uses: actions/upload-artifact@v3\n  with:\n    name: e2e-logs\n    path: e2e-logs/\n```\n\n### Local CI\n\n```bash\n# Run in CI mode\nexport E2E_CLEAN_CLUSTER=true\nexport E2E_SKIP_SETUP=false\n./test/e2e/run_e2e.sh\n```\n\n## Performance Testing\n\n### Load Testing\n\n```bash\n# Configure load test parameters\nexport E2E_CONCURRENCY=10\nexport E2E_LOAD_TEST_INVOCATIONS=100\n\n# Run stress tests\ngo test -v ./test/e2e/... -run TestConcurrentInvocations\n```\n\n### Latency Testing\n\n```bash\n# Test warm pool latency\ncurl -X POST http://localhost:8081/invoke/e2e-code-interpreter-warmpool \\\n  -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" \\\n  -d '{\"code\": \"import time; start = time.time(); print(time.time() - start)\"}'\n```\n\n## Security Considerations\n\n- Tests run with limited RBAC permissions\n- Service accounts are namespace-scoped\n- API tokens have short TTLs (24h)\n- No production credentials are used\n\n## Support\n\nFor issues or questions:\n- Check troubleshooting section\n- Review test logs in `$ARTIFACTS_PATH`\n- Open an issue on GitHub\n","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/test/e2e/README.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.\n\nLSP errors detected in other files:\n<diagnostics file=\"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/client-go/listers/runtime/v1alpha1/agentruntime.go\">\nERROR [27:16] undefined: labels\nERROR [27:37] undefined: runtimev1alpha1\nERROR [39:44] undefined: labels\nERROR [39:65] undefined: runtimev1alpha1\nERROR [40:14] undefined: runtimev1alpha1\nERROR [42:27] undefined: runtimev1alpha1\nERROR [52:16] undefined: labels\nERROR [52:37] undefined: runtimev1alpha1\nERROR [53:21] undefined: runtimev1alpha1\nERROR [61:52] undefined: labels\nERROR [61:73] undefined: runtimev1alpha1\nERROR [62:14] undefined: runtimev1alpha1\nERROR [64:27] undefined: runtimev1alpha1\nERROR [69:57] undefined: runtimev1alpha1\nERROR [72:15] undefined: errors\nERROR [72:34] undefined: runtimev1alpha1\nERROR [77:15] undefined: runtimev1alpha1\n</diagnostics>\n\nLSP errors detected in other files:\n<diagnostics file=\"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/client-go/clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/fake/fake_runtime_client.go\">\nERROR [26:3] undefined: testing\nERROR [30:9] cannot use &FakeAgentRuntimes{…} (value of type *FakeAgentRuntimes) as \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go/clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1\".AgentRuntimeInterface value in return statement: *FakeAgentRuntimes does not implement \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go/clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1\".AgentRuntimeInterface (wrong type for method Patch)\n\t\thave Patch(context.Context, string, interface{}, []byte, \"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1\".PatchOptions, ...string) (*\"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1\".AgentRuntime, error)\n\t\twant Patch(context.Context, string, types.Pat